ing from an HTMLVideoElement,\nHTMLCanvasElement (could be a WebGL canvas) or a camera/webcam/microphone\nusing getUserMedia.\n\nThe currently supported MediaStream (subclasses) are:\n: - {class}`VideoStream`: A video file/data as media stream.\n  - {class}`CameraStream`: Webcam/camera as media stream.\n  - {class}`ImageStream`: An image as a static stream.\n  - {class}`WidgetStream`: Arbitrary DOMWidget as stream.\n\nA MediaStream can be used with:\n: - {class}`VideoRecorder`: To record a movie\n  - {class}`ImageRecorder`: To create images/snapshots.\n  - {class}`AudioRecorder`: To record audio.\n  - {class}`WebRTCRoom` (or rather {class}`WebRTCRoomMqtt`): To stream a media stream to a (set of) peers.\n"]}, {"name": "ipywebrtc.webrtc.WidgetStream", "bases": ["MediaStream"], "methods": [{"name": "ipywebrtc.webrtc.WidgetStream._valid_fps", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "proposal", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}], "class_variables": [{"name": "ipywebrtc.webrtc.WidgetStream._model_name", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "ipywebrtc.webrtc.WidgetStream._view_name", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "ipywebrtc.webrtc.WidgetStream.widget", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "ipywebrtc.webrtc.WidgetStream.max_fps", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "ipywebrtc.webrtc.WidgetStream._html2canvas_start_streaming", "type": null, "documentation": []}], "instance_variables": [], "inner_classes": [], "documentation": ["Represents a widget media source.\n    "]}, {"name": "ipywebrtc.webrtc.ImageStream", "bases": ["MediaStream"], "methods": [{"name": "ipywebrtc.webrtc.ImageStream.from_file", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "cls", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "filename", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "**kwargs", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["Create a `ImageStream` from a